❯ what is this project all about                                                

● This is a Flask-based expense tracking web application called "Spendly" —
  built as a learning scaffold where students implement features step by step.

  What it is

  - A boilerplate/starter project for building an expense tracker
  - Currently has placeholder routes for all core features (auth, expenses CRUD,
  profile)
  - Students fill in the implementation across numbered "steps" (database setup,
  login, add/edit/delete expenses, etc.)

  Current state

  ┌───────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │          Feature          │                   Status                    │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Landing page              │ Template exists                             │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ User registration         │ Route + template (placeholder)              │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Login                     │ Route + template (placeholder)              │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Database                  │ database/db.py is a TODO file with comments │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Expenses                  │ Routes exist, return "coming in Step X"     │
  │ (add/edit/delete)         │ text                                        │
  ├───────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Profile / Logout          │ Placeholder routes                          │
  └───────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Tech stack

  - Backend: Flask + SQLite
  - Frontend: Jinja2 templates, CSS (custom design system with CSS variables),
  vanilla JS
  - Testing: pytest + pytest-flask

  Project name

  The brand in the UI is "Spendly" — "Track every rupee. Own your finances."

  It's essentially a guided tutorial project where you build out a full expense
  tracker feature by feature. Want me to show you what the next implementation
